I just checked this on Windows, and Ctrl-Q does the same as Ctrl-J on Mac.

Please add the output of `flutter doctor -v`. I think we'll need to get @alexander-doroshko involved, as this feature is implemented in the Dart plugin, in `DartDocumentationProvider`. Also, make sure you have the latest version of the Dart plugin. If you already have it, and want to try an experiment, try installing an earlier version.

@stevemessick Sorry, that's not what I mean.

I mean, if I go to `textfield.dart` file, line 799 (current stable), I have this:

```
  /// {@macro flutter.widgets.editableText.autofillHints}
  /// {@macro flutter.services.AutofillConfiguration.autofillHints}
  final Iterable<String>? autofillHints;
```

Then, if I put my mouse on top of the `autofillHints` and press `Ctrl-Q`, then I don't see the documentation. In other words, the @macro works in the usage, but not in the declaration. It should work everywhere.

@stevemessick Sorry, I was under the impression this is a Flutter-IntelliJ-plugin issue. Is it not? What's the criteria for filling an issue here or in https://youtrack.jetbrains.com?

@marcglasberg That's a really good question; I wish it had a simple answer. If you don't know how something is implemented it is hard to know where to file issues. The Flutter plugin adds support for Flutter-specific features, but relies on the Dart plugin for everything specific to the Dart language. The Dart plugin was created by JetBrains, so that's why Dart issues go in the JetBrains issue tracker. However, @alexander-doroshko at JetBrains is also really good at keeping tabs on issues filed here, so issues usually get moved around as needed. It is easy for us to move issues between Github repositories. The two most frequent destinations are `dart-lang/sdk` for Dart analyzer issues and `flutter/fluter` for Flutter SDK issues. It would be nice if there was an easy way to move issues to the JetBrains tracker, too.

The simple approach is to file issues here and let us figure out where they belong. Perhaps @devoncarew would have some insight here.

Without additional information we're unfortunately not sure how to resolve this issue. We're going to close this bug for now, but please don't hesitate to comment on the bug if you have any more information for us; we're happy to reopen. Thanks for your contribution!

title: Documentation references are shown instead of the documentation.
